stream
BT /F2 20 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 726 Tm (Vector Distance And Cosine Similarity) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 663 Tm (1. Why Embeddings Matter) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 616 Tm (In retrieval systems like ChromaDB, text is not compared as raw words. Instead, each) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 601 Tm (text is converted into a numeric vector called an embedding.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 563 Tm (Examples:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 525 Tm (- query: "safe weight loss") Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 508 Tm (- chunk A: "balanced diet and physical activity") Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 491 Tm (- chunk B: "dog training tips") Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 453 Tm (After embedding, each text becomes a list of numbers. Similar meanings usually produce) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 438 Tm (vectors that are closer together in vector space.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 394 Tm (2. What Vector Distance Means) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 347 Tm (Vector distance is a numeric way to measure how far two vectors are from each other.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 309 Tm (- small distance means more similar) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 292 Tm (- large distance means less similar) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 254 Tm (Think of each vector as a point in space:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 216 Tm (- nearby points mean related meaning) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 199 Tm (- far points mean unrelated meaning) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 155 Tm (3. Euclidean Distance Example) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 108 Tm (Assume a very small 2D example only for understanding:) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
