BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 736 Tm (These are different lengths, but they point in the same direction.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 698 Tm (- Euclidean distance is not zero) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 681 Tm (- cosine similarity is `1`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 643 Tm (That is why cosine similarity is often useful for embeddings.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 599 Tm (8. How This Relates To ChromaDB) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 552 Tm (In your project:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 514 Tm (1. each chunk is embedded using `all-MiniLM-L6-v2`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 497 Tm (2. the user query is embedded using the same model) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 480 Tm (3. ChromaDB compares the query vector with stored chunk vectors) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 463 Tm (4. the nearest vectors are returned) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 425 Tm (So the retrieval logic is:) Tj ET
BT /F3 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 389 Tm (query text -> query embedding) Tj ET
BT /F3 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 375 Tm (stored chunk text -> stored chunk embeddings) Tj ET
BT /F3 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 361 Tm (compare vectors) Tj ET
BT /F3 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 347 Tm (return closest chunks) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 304 Tm (9. Why The Same Embedding Model Must Be Reused) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 257 Tm (If document vectors are created by one embedding model but the query vector is created) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 242 Tm (by a different embedding model, the vectors may not live in the same space.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 204 Tm (That causes:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 166 Tm (- poor ranking) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 149 Tm (- wrong neighbors) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 132 Tm (- possible dimension mismatch) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 94 Tm (So ingestion and query must use the same embedding model.) Tj ET
endstream
