BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 579 Tm (Ranking:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 541 Tm (1. chunk A) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 524 Tm (2. chunk B) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 507 Tm (3. chunk C) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 469 Tm (That means chunk A is the closest and is retrieved first.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 425 Tm (11. In Your Code) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 378 Tm (The embedding model is configured in `rag_chromadb_demo.py` using:) Tj ET
BT /F3 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 342 Tm (SentenceTransformerEmbeddingFunction\(model_name="all-MiniLM-L6-v2"\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 305 Tm (Then the collection is queried in `retrieve_top_k\(\)`.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 267 Tm (So the process is:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 229 Tm (- Chroma gives top semantic candidates by vector similarity) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 212 Tm (- your code then reranks those candidates using `score_retrieved_chunk\(\)`) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 168 Tm (12. Final Summary) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 121 Tm (Vector distance and cosine similarity are ways to compare embeddings.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 83 Tm (- distance focuses on closeness) Tj ET
endstream
